{"CATA":[{"def":"The Latin and English form of a Greek preposition, used as a prefix to signify down, downward, under, against, contrary or opposed to, wholly, completely; as in cataclysm, catarrh.","pos":""}],"CATABAPTIST":[{"def":"One who opposes baptism, especially of infants.","pos":""}],"CATABASION":[{"def":"A vault under altar of a Greek church.","pos":""}],"CATABIOTIC":[{"def":"Aee under Force.","pos":""}],"CATACAUSTIC":[{"def":"Relating to, or having the properties of, a caustic curve formed by reflection.","pos":""}],"CATACHRESIS":[{"def":"A figure by which one word is wrongly put for another, or by which a word is wrested from its true signification; as, \"To take arms against a sea of troubles.","pos":""},{"def":"Belonging to, or in the manner of, a catachresis; wrested from its natural sense or form; forced; far-fatched.","pos":""}],"CATACLASM":[{"def":"A breaking asunder; disruption.","pos":""}],"CATACLYSM":[{"def":"Any violent catastrophe, involving sudden and extensive changes of the earth's surface.","pos":""},{"def":"Of or pertaining to a cataclysm.","pos":""}],"CATACLYSMIST":[{"def":"One who believes that the most important geological phenomena have been produced by cataclysms.","pos":""}],"CATACOMB":[{"def":"A cave, grotto, or subterraneous place of large extent used for the burial of the dead; -- commonly in the plural.","pos":""}],"CATACOUSTIC":[{"def":"That part of acoustics which treats of reflected sounds or echoes See Acoustics.","pos":""}],"CATACROTIC":[{"def":"Designating, pertaining to, or characterized by, that form of pulse tracing, or sphygmogram, in which the descending portion of the curve is marked by secondary elevations due to two or more expansions of the artery in the same beat.","pos":""}],"CATADICROTISM":[{"def":"Quality or state of being catacrotic.","pos":""},{"def":"Pertaining to, produced by, or involving, both the reflection and refraction of light; as, a catadioptric light.","pos":""}],"CATADIOPTRICS":[{"def":"The science which treats of catadioptric phenomena, or of the used of catadioptric instruments.","pos":""}],"CATADROME":[{"def":"A machine for raising or lowering heavy weights.","pos":""}],"CATADROMOUS":[{"def":"Having the lowest inferior segment of a pinna nearer the rachis than the lowest superior one; -- said of a mode of branching in ferns, and opposed to anadromous.","pos":""},{"def":"Living in fresh water, and going to the sea to spawn; -- opposed to anadromous, and of the eel.","pos":""}],"CATAFALQUE":[{"def":"A temporary structure sometimes used in the funeral solemnities of eminent persons, for the public exhibition of the remains, or their conveyance to the place of burial.","pos":""}],"CATAGMATIC":[{"def":"Having the quality of consolidating broken bones.","pos":""}],"CATAIAN":[{"def":"A native of Cathay or China; a foreigner; -- formerly a term of reproach.","pos":""}],"CATALAN":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to Catalonia.","pos":""},{"def":"A native or inbabitant of Catalonia; also, the language of Catalonia.","pos":""}],"CATALECTIC":[{"def":"Wanting a syllable at the end, or terminating in an imperfect foot; as, a catalectic verse.","pos":""},{"def":"Incomplete; partial; not affecting the whole of a substance.","pos":""}],"CATALEPTIC":[{"def":"Pertaining to, or resembling, catalepsy; affected with catalepsy; as, a cataleptic fit.","pos":""}],"CATALLACTA":[{"def":"A division of Protozoa, of which Magosphæra is the type.","pos":""}],"CATALLACTICS":[{"def":"The science of exchanges, a branch of political economy.","pos":""}],"CATALOGIZE":[{"def":"To insert in a catalogue; to register; to catalogue.","pos":""}],"CATALOGUE":[{"def":"A list or enumeration of names, or articles arranged methodically, often in alphabetical order; as, a catalogue of the students of a college, or of books, or of the stars.","pos":""}],"CATALOGUER":[{"def":"A maker of catalogues; esp.","pos":""}],"CATALPA":[{"def":"A genus of American and East Indian trees, of which the best know species are the Catalpa bignonioides, a large, ornamental North American tree, with spotted white flowers and long cylindrical pods, and the C.","pos":""}],"CATALYSIS":[{"def":"Dissolution; degeneration; decay.","pos":""}],"CATALYTIC":[{"def":"Relating to, or causing, catalysis.","pos":""}],"CATAMARAN":[{"def":"A kind of raft or float, consisting of two or more logs or pieces of wood lashed together, and moved by paddles or sail; -- used as a surf boat and for other purposes on the coasts of the East and West Indies and South America.","pos":""},{"def":"Any vessel with twin hulls, whether propelled by sails or by steam; esp.","pos":""}],"CATAMENIA":[{"def":"The monthly courses of women; menstrual discharges; menses.","pos":""}],"CATAMENIAL":[{"def":"Pertaining to the catamenia, or menstrual discharges.","pos":""}],"CATAMITE":[{"def":"A boy kept for unnatural purposes.","pos":""}],"CATANADROMOUS":[{"def":"Ascending and descending fresh streams from and to the sea, as the salmon; anadromous.","pos":""}],"CATAPASM":[{"def":"A compound medicinal powder, used by the ancients to sprinkle on ulcers, to absorb perspiration, etc.","pos":""}],"CATAPELTIC":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to a catapult.","pos":""}],"CATAPETALOUS":[{"def":"Having the petals held together by stamens, which grow to their bases, as in the mallow.","pos":""}],"CATAPHONIC":[{"def":"Of or relating to cataphonics; catacoustic.","pos":""}],"CATAPHONICS":[{"def":"That branch of acoustics which treats of reflested sounds; catacoustics.","pos":""}],"CATAPHRACT":[{"def":"Defensive armor used for the whole body and often for the horse, also, esp.","pos":""},{"def":"The armor or plate covering some fishes.","pos":""}],"CATAPHRACTED":[{"def":"Covered with a cataphract, or armor of plates, scales, etc.","pos":""}],"CATAPHRACTIC":[{"def":"Of, pertaining to, or resembling, a cataphract.","pos":""}],"CATAPHYSICAL":[{"def":"Unnatural; contrary to nature.","pos":""}],"CATAPLASM":[{"def":"A soft and moist substance applied externally to some part of the body; a poultice.","pos":""}],"CATAPLEXY":[{"def":"A morbid condition caused by an overwhelming shock or extreme fear and marked by rigidity of the muscles.","pos":""}],"CATAPULT":[{"def":"An engine somewhat resembling a massive crossbow, used by the ancient Greeks and Romans for throwing stones, arrows, spears, etc.","pos":""}],"CATARACT":[{"def":"An opacity of the crystalline lens, or of its capsule, which prevents the passage of the rays of light and impairs or destroys the sight.","pos":""},{"def":"A kind of hydraulic brake for regulating the action of pumping engines and other machines; -- sometimes called dashpot.","pos":""}],"CATARACTOUS":[{"def":"Of the nature of a cataract in the eye; affected with cataract.","pos":""}],"CATARRH":[{"def":"An inflammatory affection of any mucous membrane, in which there are congestion, swelling, and an altertion in the quantity and quality of mucus secreted; as catarrh of the stomach; catarrh of the bladder.","pos":""}],"CATARRHAL":[{"def":"Pertaining to, produced by, or attending, catarrh; of the nature of catarrh.","pos":""}],"CATARRHINE":[{"def":"One of the Catarrhina, a division of Quadrumana, including the Old World monkeys and apes which have the nostrils close together and turned downward.","pos":""}],"CATASTALTIC":[{"def":"Checking evacutions through astringent or styptic qualities.","pos":""}],"CATASTASIS":[{"def":"That part of a speech, usually the exordium, in which the orator sets forth the subject matter to be discussed.","pos":""},{"def":"The state, or condition of anything; constitution; habit of body.","pos":""}],"CATASTERISM":[{"def":"A placing among the stars; a catalogue of stars.","pos":""}],"CATASTROPHE":[{"def":"A violent and widely extended change in the surface of the earth, as, an elevation or subsidence of some part of it, effected by internal causes.","pos":""}],"CATASTROPHIC":[{"def":"Of a pertaining to a catastrophe.","pos":""}],"CATASTROPHISM":[{"def":"The doctrine that the geological changes in the earth's crust have been caused by the sudden action of violent physical causes; -- opposed to the doctrine of uniformism.","pos":""}],"CATASTROPHIST":[{"def":"One who holds the theory or catastrophism.","pos":""}],"CATAWBA":[{"def":"A well known light red variety of American grape.","pos":""},{"def":"A light-colored, sprightly American wine from the Catawba grape.","pos":""}]}